					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">It always seems to happen close to a screen transition (when entering a warp, when a level has been finished), so I'm going to guess that it's an artifact from doing <em>something</em> with PPU (e.g. turning off rendering momentarily) when the rendering happens to be in the middle of the screen. Hard to say what exactly, but doppel's SMB disassembly should have the answer. Might be hard to find though if it's not reproducible.<br /><br />Technically I don't see a reason why it shouldn't also happen on emulators.</div>

					
